article.headline: American U. 68, Colgate 60
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Garrison Carr scored 24 points to lead American University in a 68-60 win over Colgate Sunday. Derrick Mercer contributed 18 points for American (16-10, 8-3 Patriot League). American trailed 34-25 at halftime, but rebounded in the second half. They took the lead at the 13:20 mark on one of six three-pointers by Carr. Colgate built up its first quarter lead with solid shooting, hitting 13-of-24 and four-of-eight from behind the arc. Kyle Roemer led Colgate (12-13, 4-7 PL) with 20 points and Kendall Chones contributed 10. The Eagles' comeback started early in the second half, when Bryce Simon hit a three-pointer. Travis Lay followed up with a three-point play to cut the deficit to three points less than two minutes into the half.
